WHAT GOES IN EACH FILE

docker-compose.yml — defines all services for local development. PostgreSQL, Neo4j, Redis, your FastAPI app, Celery worker, Celery Beat scheduler. One command — docker-compose up — starts everything locally.

.env — your secrets and configuration. Never committed to Git. Contains Azure Key Vault URL, Microsoft Graph API credentials, PostgreSQL connection string, Neo4j credentials, Redis URL, Azure OpenAI key.

.env.example — same structure as .env but with placeholder values. This IS committed to Git so collaborators know what variables are needed without seeing your actual secrets.

requirements.txt — all Python dependencies. Key ones for Component 0 — fastapi, uvicorn, sqlalchemy, alembic, psycopg2-binary, pgvector, neo4j, redis, celery, msal, requests, beautifulsoup4, email-reply-parser, spacy, presidio-analyzer, presidio-anonymizer, azure-keyvault-secrets, azure-identity, cryptography, pydantic, python-dotenv, structlog.

alembic.ini — configuration for Alembic database migrations. Points to your PostgreSQL connection string.

alembic/versions/001_initial_schema.py — your first database migration. Creates all tables in the correct order respecting foreign key constraints. Runs with one command — alembic upgrade head.

app/main.py — FastAPI application entry point. Registers all routers. Sets up startup and shutdown events — database connection pool initialisation, Neo4j connection, Redis connection.

app/config.py — reads all environment variables using pydantic-settings. Single source of truth for all configuration. Every other file imports settings from here, never reads environment variables directly.

app/dependencies.py — FastAPI dependency injection functions. get_db returns a PostgreSQL session. get_neo4j returns a Neo4j session. get_current_user reads JWT token from request header and returns the authenticated user. get_redis returns Redis client. These are injected into API route handlers automatically by FastAPI.

app/core/security.py — JWT token creation and verification for your own API authentication. Separate from Microsoft OAuth — this is how your frontend authenticates to your ContextIQ backend.

app/core/encryption.py — AES-256 encryption and decryption functions using Azure Key Vault managed keys. Used by pii_handler and anywhere sensitive data is stored.

app/core/audit.py — write_audit_log function. Called by every sensitive operation throughout the system. Takes action_type, resource_type, resource_id, outcome, user_token. Writes to audit_log table. Never throws exceptions — audit logging failure should never break the main operation.

app/core/exceptions.py — custom exception classes. IngestionError, PiiHandlingError, GraphSeedingError, TokenRefreshError. Structured exceptions with error codes that map to HTTP responses.

app/db/postgres.py — SQLAlchemy engine and session factory. Connection pooling via PgBouncer URL. Session lifecycle management.

app/db/neo4j.py — Neo4j driver initialisation. Connection pooling. Session factory.

app/db/redis.py — Redis client initialisation. Connection pooling.

app/db/models/ — one file per database table. Each file contains a SQLAlchemy model class defining the table schema. These models are what Alembic reads to generate migrations.

app/ingestion/providers/base.py — abstract EmailProvider class. Defines the interface — fetch_messages, get_thread, mark_processed, get_delta. No implementation here.

app/ingestion/providers/outlook.py — OutlookProvider class inheriting from EmailProvider. All Microsoft Graph API logic lives here. MSAL authentication, token refresh, delta query, pagination, error handling. Returns standardised EmailMessage objects regardless of Microsoft's response format.

app/ingestion/providers/gmail.py — GmailProvider stub. Has the class definition and method signatures but raises NotImplementedError for everything. Shows the adapter pattern is designed even though Gmail isn't implemented. Perfect interview talking point.

app/ingestion/cleaner.py — EmailCleaner class. Takes raw email body. Strips HTML with BeautifulSoup. Removes quoted replies with email-reply-parser. Strips signatures. Strips legal disclaimers. Returns clean text.

app/ingestion/thread_builder.py — ThreadBuilder class. Takes an email and builds or updates thread records in PostgreSQL. Handles conversationId grouping. Updates email counts and timestamps.

app/ingestion/entity_extractor.py — EntityExtractor class. Takes clean email body. Runs spaCy NER. Returns list of extracted entities with types and values.

app/ingestion/thread_linker.py — ThreadLinker class. Takes extracted entities and current thread. Applies four rules to find candidate thread relationships. Creates thread_relationship records for matches.

app/security/pii_handler.py — PiiHandler class. Takes raw email body. Runs Presidio analyzer to find PII. For each entity — calls vault to get or create token. Replaces PII in text with tokens. Returns pseudonymised text and list of replacements made.

app/security/vault.py — PiiVault class. Manages pii_vault table. get_or_create_token takes entity type and value, returns existing token or creates new one. reverse_token takes token and returns original value — only callable by authorised roles, writes to audit log every time.

app/security/key_vault.py — AzureKeyVaultClient class. Wraps azure-keyvault-secrets. get_secret, set_secret, delete_secret methods. Used by encryption.py and vault.py. All Azure Key Vault interactions go through this class.

app/graph/seeder.py — GraphSeeder class. Takes processed email data. Creates or updates Person, Thread, Message nodes in Neo4j. Creates SENT, INVOLVES, MENTIONS edges. Stores Neo4j node IDs back in PostgreSQL records.

app/graph/queries.py — predefined Cypher queries for Component 0 specific graph operations. find_person_by_token, create_thread_node, link_person_to_thread. Later components add their own queries to this file.

app/tasks/celery_app.py — Celery application initialisation. Configures Redis as broker. Defines four queues — ingestion, intelligence, analytics, notifications. Sets task retry policies and dead letter queue.

app/tasks/ingestion_tasks.py — Celery tasks for ingestion. process_mailbox_sync task — called per mailbox per sync cycle. process_single_email task — called per email. Each task is atomic — if it fails, only that email or that mailbox sync fails, not the entire batch.

app/tasks/scheduled_tasks.py — Celery Beat scheduled tasks. sync_all_mailboxes runs every 15 minutes. Fetches all active mailboxes from PostgreSQL. Dispatches process_mailbox_sync task for each one.

app/api/routers/workspaces.py — FastAPI router for workspace CRUD. POST /workspaces creates workspace. GET /workspaces lists workspaces for current user. All routes require authentication. Admin only routes use RBAC dependency.

app/api/routers/mailboxes.py — FastAPI router for mailbox management. POST /workspaces/{id}/mailboxes triggers OAuth flow and registers mailbox. GET /workspaces/{id}/mailboxes lists mailboxes. DELETE /workspaces/{id}/mailboxes/{mailbox_id} revokes token and removes mailbox.

app/api/routers/auth.py — FastAPI router for authentication. POST /auth/login returns JWT. POST /auth/refresh refreshes JWT. POST /auth/logout revokes session.

app/api/schemas/ — Pydantic schemas for request and response validation. Separate from SQLAlchemy models. Request schemas validate incoming data. Response schemas control what gets returned — never expose raw database models directly to API consumers.

tests/conftest.py — pytest fixtures shared across all tests. test_db fixture creates an in-memory test database. test_client fixture creates a FastAPI test client. mock_graph fixture mocks Neo4j. mock_redis fixture mocks Redis. mock_presidio fixture mocks PII detection.

tests/unit/test_cleaner.py — tests for EmailCleaner. Test HTML stripping. Test quoted reply removal. Test signature stripping. Test legal disclaimer removal. All tests use static email strings — no external dependencies.

tests/unit/test_pii_handler.py — tests for PiiHandler. Test that person names are pseudonymised. Test that email addresses are tokenised. Test that the same entity always gets the same token. Test that cleaned text contains no original PII. Mock Presidio and vault calls.

tests/unit/test_entity_extractor.py — tests for EntityExtractor. Test date extraction. Test person name extraction as tokens. Test that extraction works on various email formats. Mock spaCy to avoid loading model in unit tests.

tests/unit/test_thread_linker.py — tests for ThreadLinker. Test each of the four linking rules independently. Test that low confidence matches don't create relationships. Test that cross-workspace matching is prevented.

tests/unit/test_thread_builder.py — tests for ThreadBuilder. Test new thread creation. Test existing thread update. Test email count increment. Test conversationId grouping.

tests/integration/test_ingestion_pipeline.py — end to end test of full pipeline. Uses test database. Mocks Microsoft Graph API responses with realistic email JSON. Verifies emails correctly land in PostgreSQL with PII pseudonymised. Verifies thread relationships created correctly.

tests/integration/test_graph_seeder.py — integration test for Neo4j seeding. Uses test Neo4j instance. Verifies Person nodes created. Verifies Thread nodes created. Verifies edges created correctly. Verifies node IDs stored back in PostgreSQL.

